
// The Hyperlambda code sends a signal to a specific role using the [sockets.signal] slot. It targets the "root" role and transmits a message indicating that the training of an OpenAI model has failed, with the message type specified as "error". The [roles] slot specifies the recipient role, while the [args] slot contains the message details.
sockets.signal:magic.backend.message
   roles:root
   args
      message:Training of your OpenAI model FAILED!
      type:error
